  "text": "The Grafana unified alerting rule evaluation and notification chain follows this flow:\n\n1. **Rule Scheduler** (pkg/services/ngalert/schedule/schedule.go:Run): The scheduler runs periodically, fetching alert rules and scheduling their evaluation at configured intervals.\n\n2. **Alert Rule Evaluation** (pkg/services/ngalert/schedule/alert_rule.go:run and evaluate): For each alert rule, the scheduler creates a goroutine that calls the evaluate() method. This method:\n   - Creates an evaluator using eval.EvaluatorFactory\n   - Calls ruleEval.Evaluate() (pkg/services/ngalert/eval/eval.go) to execute the query conditions\n   - Passes evaluation results to the state manager\n\n3. **Alert State Transition** (pkg/services/ngalert/state/manager.go:ProcessEvalResults): The state manager processes evaluation results:\n   - Calls setNextStateForRule() to determine the new state for each alert instance based on current and previous states\n   - Handles state transitions (Normal, Pending, Alerting, ResolvedAt)\n   - Creates StateTransition objects representing changes\n   - Updates alert state cache and persists to database\n\n4. **Alert State Representation** (pkg/services/ngalert/state/state.go:State): Each alert instance maintains state including:\n   - Current state (Normal, Pending, Alerting, Error, NoData)\n   - Labels and annotations\n   - FiredAt timestamp (when transitioned to Alerting)\n   - ResolvedAt timestamp (when transitioned back to Normal)\n\n5. **Alert Notification Dispatch** (pkg/services/ngalert/schedule/alert_rule.go:send): After state processing:\n   - State transitions are converted to PostableAlerts\n   - Passed to AlertsSender interface (AlertsRouter implementation in pkg/services/ngalert/sender/router.go)\n   - Router determines routing based on org configuration (internal Alertmanager vs external)\n\n6. **Organization-specific Alertmanager Routing** (pkg/services/ngalert/notifier/multiorg_alertmanager.go:AlertmanagerFor): The MultiOrgAlertmanager:\n   - Maps each organization to its own Alertmanager instance\n   - Routes alerts to the correct org's Alertmanager\n\n7. **Alert Ingestion** (pkg/services/ngalert/notifier/alertmanager.go:PutAlerts): The alertmanager receives alerts and:\n   - Receives PostableAlerts with state transitions\n   - Routes alerts through the Alertmanager's alert routing tree\n   - Applies silences and inhibition rules\n\n8. **External Alertmanager Dispatch** (pkg/services/ngalert/sender/notifier.go:Manager and pkg/services/ngalert/sender/sender.go:ExternalAlertmanager):\n   - For organizations with external Alertmanager configured, alerts are dispatched to external systems\n   - Uses Prometheus-compatible alert format\n   - Batches alerts for efficient transmission\n\nThe entire chain is coordinated in pkg/services/ngalert/ngalert.go (AlertNG service), which initializes and wires together all components: scheduler, evaluator factory, state manager, and alerting routers."
