nager:\n   - Maps each organization to its own Alertmanager instance\n   - Routes alerts to the correct org's Alertmanager\n\n7. **Alert Ingestion** (pkg/services/ngalert/notifier/alertmanager.go:PutAlerts): The alertmanager receives alerts and:\n   - Receives PostableAlerts with state transitions\n   - Routes alerts through the Alertmanager's alert routing tree\n   - Applies silences and inhibition rules\n\n8. **External Alertmanager Dispatch** (pkg/services/ngalert/sender/notifier.go:Manager and pkg/services/ngalert/sender/sender.go:ExternalAlertmanager):\n   - For organizations with external Alertmanager configured, alerts are dispatched to external systems\n   - Uses Prometheus-compatible alert format\n   - Batches alerts for efficient transmission\n\nThe entire chain is coordinated in pkg/services/ngalert/ngalert.go (AlertNG service), which initializes and wires together all components: scheduler, evaluator factory, state manager, and alerting routers."
